From b43ed1ba9359275fee19a115659da79524135253 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 20:55:58 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] fix(sw): activate new app versions at next safe
 navigation boundary
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Tabs that were open during a deploy kept rendering with the previously
hashed CSS/JS bundles because nothing in the app subscribed to
SwUpdate.versionUpdates and the SW's index.html fallback served the
cached app shell to every SPA route. The visible symptom was broken
.prose layout (tables, code blocks, mermaid placeholders) until a hard
refresh.

AppUpdateService now drives a single "reload at next safe boundary"
state machine fed by two independent triggers — Angular's SwUpdate
events and a 5-min poll of a build-time /version.json stamp — so we
also catch the cases where the SW itself is stale, disabled, or never
activates within the visit window. The reload fires immediately while
the user is idle (scrollY===0), defers to the next NavigationEnd or
visibilitychange→visible otherwise, and falls back to clearing every
Cache Storage bucket on UNRECOVERABLE_STATE.

Also tightens registerWhenStable from 30s to 5s so short visits give
the SW a real shot at registering, and pins /version.json behind
nginx Cache-Control: no-cache + an ngsw freshness dataGroup so neither
the CDN nor the SW can serve a stale stamp past a deploy.

