From c9e18bd94045f6fe59c39a718262f89913824f0f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 21:00:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/7] fix(sidebar): hide labels in tablet @media so collapsed
 icons stay visible
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The G1 collapse refactor compressed the rail to 60 px via host transform
scaleX(--sidebar-scale) and counter-scaled the children, with two paths
turning that on:

  - Runtime: the .collapsed host class (driven by [collapsed]() input)
    fires the existing :host(.collapsed) rules, which hide labels via
    display:none so .nav-item's justify-content:center centres just
    the icon — landing it dead-centre in the visible 60 px window.
  - SSR / pre-hydration: the @media (min-width:768px) and (max-width:
    1023px) block was meant to render the same collapsed visuals
    independent of the host class so the prerendered HTML matches
    every viewport, but only re-emitted --sidebar-scale, the avatar
    size, and .nav-item padding/justify. With labels still in flow,
    .nav-item's flex group (icon + gap + label + gap + ext ≈ 152 px)
    centred inside the un-scaled 244 px row, putting the icon's left
    edge at ~58 px of original coords — past the visible rail's right
    edge. Result: empty 60 px strip with no icons in tablet width.

Mirror the rest of :host(.collapsed)'s display rules inside the @media
block (.identity / .nav-label / .nav-ext / .divider-label / button
spans hidden, divider + footer paddings collapsed) so the SSR path
produces the same icon-only rail as the JS path. Spec coverage for
the runtime path is unchanged and still green.

