at x=0, so the composed transform is identity — list-local x equals
viewport x. With `justify-content: center` on `.nav-item` (a 244 px row),
the icon was landing at viewport x ≈ 121 — past the visible 60 px rail.

Drop `justify-content: center` from the collapsed-state `.nav-item` (both
the `:host(.collapsed)` rule and the tablet `@media` mirror) and add an
explicit `justify-content: flex-start` on `:host(.collapsed)` /
`@media` `.theme-toggle, .resume-btn` to override the baseline centring.
