From 6bc2c247750a6273f43535edf2245437f53648cd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Faisal Khan <mfkhan@sofi.org>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 21:47:29 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 6/7] fix(layout): hide heading permalink anchor on mobile to
 keep heading text anchored to the column edge
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The previous attempt at mobile heading-anchor alignment (16de4f1b) only
addressed the vertical alignment of the icon — it was still rendered
inline at the start of the heading via `position: static`, which meant
revealing it on hover/focus visibly shifted the heading text rightward
by ~30 px. Desktop never has that problem because it uses
`position: absolute; left: calc(-1 * var(--space-6))` to park the icon
in the gutter to the left of the column.

There's no equivalent gutter on mobile to host the icon, and every
in-flow alternative trades one usability problem for another (clipping
outside the viewport at small widths, stranding the icon at the
heading's right edge far from where it permalinks to, overlaying the
icon on the leading letters, permanently indenting every mobile
heading away from the column edge).

The pattern this design takes inspiration from (GitHub, MDN, Stripe
Docs, Tailwind Docs, Vercel Docs, Docusaurus and Astro Starlight
defaults) all converge on the same answer: the heading-anchor reveal
is a desktop-only affordance. On mobile, users copy the section URL
from the address bar plus the native share sheet — the chain icon is
a hover-style interaction that touch screens don't reliably surface.

Replace the existing `@media (max-width: 900px) .prose .anchor` rule
body with `display: none` and document the rationale inline. The
functional half of the permalink is unaffected — every heading still
emits `id="..."` from `MarkdownService.heading`, so `/post#section`
deep links continue to scroll-anchor on every viewport.

Verified with npm run lint and markdown.service.spec (16 tests). The
spec asserts the anchor markup shape, not its CSS, so no spec changes
were needed.

Made-with: Cursor
